Many who have gained fame
hide behind their black deeds.

1077
01:20:21,792 --> 01:20:24,000
At least you are covered in white.

1078
01:20:24,250 --> 01:20:25,458
You are crazy.

1079
01:20:37,333 --> 01:20:38,708
Happy Birthday.

1080
01:20:40,708 --> 01:20:43,500
- What are you doing! - To you too!

1081
01:20:48,333 --> 01:20:49,250
Hello!

1082
01:20:53,917 --> 01:20:56,500
Hey guys, stop press now!

1083
01:20:56,583 --> 01:20:58,625
Anything new about Silk?

1084
01:20:58,708 --> 01:21:01,333
I have something that
will create a sensation.

1085
01:21:01,417 --> 01:21:03,875
Tell us, Nayla. What did Silk do now?

1086
01:21:04,667 --> 01:21:06,000
I haven't thought about it.

1087
01:21:06,083 --> 01:21:07,375
About what?

1088
01:21:07,500 --> 01:21:10,000
What do I label Silk?

1089
01:21:10,458 --> 01:21:12,667
Manipulative or helpless?

1090
01:21:13,208 --> 01:21:15,958
Vamp or just a victim?

1091
01:21:18,167 --> 01:21:19,708
How are the pictures?

1092
01:21:20,125 --> 01:21:21,458
I'll cut them out.

1093
01:21:21,542 --> 01:21:23,667
What about the
rubbish written about us?

1094
01:21:25,125 --> 01:21:27,458
I don't know what has been written.

1095
01:21:27,708 --> 01:21:30,167
In fact, I don't care and never did!

1096
01:21:31,042 --> 01:21:34,417
I cut out the pictures,
but only if they are good.

1097
01:21:34,542 --> 01:21:37,083
A newspaper may go stale in a day...

1098
01:21:38,042 --> 01:21:40,417
but the news in it remains
fresh for years to come.

1099
01:21:42,000 --> 01:21:44,875
And these journalists never
write anything good about you.

1100
01:21:47,042 --> 01:21:48,792
Now they've labelled you Draupadi.

1101
01:22:38,792 --> 01:22:39,917
Ma'am...

1102
01:22:41,208 --> 01:22:42,625
Nayla madam is busy at the party.

1103
01:22:42,708 --> 01:22:46,208
She said she can't meet anyone
and I shouldn't let anyone in.

1104
01:22:46,833 --> 01:22:48,500
Didn't you tell her it's Silk?

1105
01:22:48,583 --> 01:22:51,208
Yes, ma'am, I know you. I told her.

1106
01:22:52,333 --> 01:22:53,792
What's this party about?

1107
01:22:53,875 --> 01:22:56,708
Ma'am, the party is to celebrate
Nayla madam's best journalist award.

1108
01:22:56,833 --> 01:22:58,333
A lot of high profile people
and celebrities are present.

1109
01:23:00,417 --> 01:23:01,667
Thank you.

1110
01:23:44,042 --> 01:23:45,375
Kumar...

1111
01:23:48,917 --> 01:23:50,208
call the police.

1112
01:23:54,958 --> 01:23:56,750
I guess they heard I'm on the way.

1113
01:23:56,833 --> 01:23:57,958
Yes, sir.

1114
01:23:58,000 --> 01:23:59,708
But they are looking in
the opposite direction.

1115
01:24:03,583 --> 01:24:06,375
Honk... honk!
Otherwise they won't give way.

1116
01:24:37,125 --> 01:24:39,792
I can't stay here like these idiots.

1117
01:24:40,333 --> 01:24:41,458
Let's go back.

1118
01:24:41,542 --> 01:24:42,875
I'll check what's going on.

1119
01:25:11,375 --> 01:25:12,833
Are you alright?

1120
01:25:13,083 --> 01:25:14,208
What are you doing?

1121
01:25:14,375 --> 01:25:16,208
Stealing the thunder
from Nayla's party.

1122
01:25:17,208 --> 01:25:18,958
You are unbelievable, Silk.

1123
01:25:25,000 --> 01:25:28,833
Why ruin just one party,
when I can ruin two!

1124
01:25:48,875 --> 01:25:50,792
Driver, start the car... come on!

1125
01:26:02,083 --> 01:26:04,667
There are many stars in
this industry, Silk...

1126
01:26:05,833 --> 01:26:08,917
but there's only one hero
- you.

1127
01:26:13,083 --> 01:26:14,500
That was unbelievable.

1128
01:26:17,708 --> 01:26:20,542
You publicly wrecked
her private party.

1129
01:26:20,625 --> 01:26:23,667
Now Nayla will never celebrate
anything, not even her birthday!

1130
01:26:24,583 --> 01:26:27,875
Once Silk decides on something,
she goes through with it.

1131
01:26:27,958 --> 01:26:29,208
Surya, for instance.

1132
01:26:29,375 --> 01:26:32,000
His mouth was open
like an uncovered manhole.

1133
01:26:35,667 --> 01:26:37,250
I hope you didn't mind...

1134
01:26:38,000 --> 01:26:40,083
me kissing you.

1135
01:26:41,875 --> 01:26:44,083
My heart said so and I did.

1136
01:26:44,792 --> 01:26:46,542
Even though the
heart is on the left...

1137
01:26:47,708 --> 01:26:50,333
its decisions are always right.

1138
01:26:52,792 --> 01:26:56,250
Wow, the writer rises...

1139
01:26:56,958 --> 01:26:58,667
You should sleep.

1140
01:26:59,333 --> 01:27:02,000
Tomorrow I have
narrate the story to Vijayan.

1141
01:27:02,375 --> 01:27:04,417
And you have a shoot too.

1142
01:27:05,583 --> 01:27:07,750
We just left two
people burning with anger...

1143
01:27:08,250 --> 01:27:10,167
and you want to put it out?

1144
01:27:10,708 --> 01:27:14,083
If I stay back, a fire
will start over here.

1145
01:27:16,042 --> 01:27:17,333
Then let it.

1146
01:27:25,792 --> 01:27:27,708
Ooh lala, Ooh lala

1147
01:27:27,792 --> 01:27:30,500
You are my...

1148
01:27:31,042 --> 01:27:33,333
You don't call out to
others when you're on the edge.

1149
01:27:36,500 --> 01:27:37,875
The bullet exits the gun...

1150
01:27:38,250 --> 01:27:39,958
The villain's spirit exits his body...

1151
01:27:40,458 --> 01:27:42,000
The end of the film.

1152
01:27:42,083 --> 01:27:43,375
And the audience exits the theater.

1153
01:27:43,458 --> 01:27:45,000
What kind of ending is this?

1154
01:27:45,458 --> 01:27:47,250
I didn't even have a fight sequence.

1155
01:27:48,083 --> 01:27:51,000
Swords are pulled
out of their sheath...

1156
01:27:51,083 --> 01:27:53,250
Clothes ripped apart...

1157
01:27:53,750 --> 01:27:55,417
Bodies ripped apart... Blood all over.

1158
01:27:55,500 --> 01:27:57,250
That leads to the end of the film.

1159
01:27:57,375 --> 01:28:00,583
You should have a sword fight,
yes a sword fight.

1160
01:28:00,667 --> 01:28:02,833
Sir, the lead hero is a cop.

1161
01:28:03,208 --> 01:28:05,208
How could he have a sword?

1162
01:28:07,000 --> 01:28:09,458
That's a valid point.

1163
01:28:10,333 --> 01:28:11,875
Perhaps an ancestral sword...

1164
01:28:12,500 --> 01:28:14,000
a family heirloom.

1165
01:28:15,708 --> 01:28:17,542
But, Sir... the lead
hero is an orphan.

1166
01:28:17,667 --> 01:28:18,833
Boring!

1167
01:28:20,167 --> 01:28:22,000
Boring!

1168
01:28:23,000 --> 01:28:26,833
Lead heroes of the 60s
and 70s were orphans.

1169
01:28:27,125 --> 01:28:29,583
We are in the 80s now.

1170
01:28:30,208 --> 01:28:33,792
Let him have a family.

1171
01:28:34,583 --> 01:28:35,917
And a sister...

1172
01:28:36,333 --> 01:28:37,583
give her dignity...

1173
01:28:37,667 --> 01:28:38,958
And then take it away!

1174
01:28:39,417 --> 01:28:43,333
His sister's trampled dignity...

1175
01:28:43,958 --> 01:28:47,083
should reflect on his sword.

1176
01:28:47,417 --> 01:28:49,833
Now that will heighten the climax!

1177
01:28:49,917 --> 01:28:51,042
What do you say, Vijayan?

1178
01:28:51,125 --> 01:28:53,583
Sir, what an imagination!

1179
01:28:53,667 --> 01:28:55,875
Genius... Sir, you're a genius!

1180
01:28:56,250 --> 01:29:00,458
It's a curse, Vijayan. It's a curse!

1181
01:29:01,417 --> 01:29:03,500
What do you think, Rama?

1182
01:29:04,667 --> 01:29:06,000
I have one word...

1183
01:29:07,333 --> 01:29:08,500
Superhit!

1184
01:29:09,542 --> 01:29:12,250
Sir, sensational, this
will be sensational!

1185
01:29:12,708 --> 01:29:15,458
Silk couldn't differentiate
between a man and a horse.

1186
01:29:15,917 --> 01:29:19,042
A horse at its peak will win derbies.

1187
01:29:21,000 --> 01:29:24,792
But a man at his peak
moves like time itself.

1188
01:29:25,125 --> 01:29:28,000
Then he can neither stop.

1189
01:29:35,750 --> 01:29:37,833
Do you remember...
when we first met...

1190
01:29:38,667 --> 01:29:40,375
you couldn't utter a word.

1191
01:29:41,375 --> 01:29:43,458
And now you make excuses!

1192
01:29:48,000 --> 01:29:51,667
There was a time when I'd merely
think of you and you would show up.

1193
01:29:53,042 --> 01:29:54,417
And now...

1194
01:29:54,500 --> 01:29:56,208
you think twice before meeting me.

1195
01:29:56,333 --> 01:29:57,583
Cut it!

1196
01:29:59,333 --> 01:30:00,583
What are you laughing for?

1197
01:30:00,667 --> 01:30:03,000
You think this is a joke?

1198
01:30:03,083 --> 01:30:04,917
You are the one making a joke, madam.

1199
01:30:05,417 --> 01:30:07,417
We shot this scene yesterday.

1200
01:30:09,625 --> 01:30:11,000
I need a cigarette!

1201
01:30:11,083 --> 01:30:12,250
Silk...

1202
01:30:12,375 --> 01:30:13,958
what's going on?

1203
01:30:14,542 --> 01:30:16,417
Once upon a time,
you'd act out a scene and..

1204
01:30:16,500 --> 01:30:18,000
..I didn't feel like calling
out ‘cut'.

1205
01:30:18,583 --> 01:30:20,875
But it seems like you
don't feel like acting anymore.

1206
01:30:20,958 --> 01:30:22,500
How can I?

1207
01:30:22,583 --> 01:30:24,167
There's nothing new to do.

1208
01:30:24,250 --> 01:30:27,667
Everyday it's the same old scene,
same old dialogue, same old story.

1209
01:30:27,750 --> 01:30:30,583
You can only act in
one particular film...

1210
01:30:30,667 --> 01:30:32,000
and I'll make it.

1211
01:30:34,417 --> 01:30:38,083
I know why you're so arrogant today.

1212
01:30:38,167 --> 01:30:40,958
You've signed on
that new girl, Shakeela.

1213
01:30:41,000 --> 01:30:42,500
But Venkat sir...

1214
01:30:42,917 --> 01:30:44,958
there can never be another Silk.

1215
01:30:45,000 --> 01:30:46,542
And we don't want another Silk!

1216
01:30:46,667 --> 01:30:47,875
Everyday it's something new.

1217
01:30:47,958 --> 01:30:49,500
A new spat with Surya...

1218
01:30:49,583 --> 01:30:51,000
or a new scene with his brother.

1219
01:30:51,083 --> 01:30:52,833
Or your love for the bottle.

1220
01:30:52,958 --> 01:30:54,708
In that case, ‘pack up'!

1221
01:30:59,167 --> 01:31:00,667
Make this film with that...

1222
01:31:00,750 --> 01:31:03,542
that girl... Shakeela!

1223
01:31:03,625 --> 01:31:05,167
Silk, wait,

1224
01:31:05,250 --> 01:31:06,958
don't make a mistake. you'll regret.

1225
01:31:07,000 --> 01:31:09,375
People who walk out on their work...

1226
01:31:09,458 --> 01:31:11,708
spend the rest of their
lives begging for work.

1227
01:31:11,792 --> 01:31:13,125
But they get nothing.

1228
01:31:13,208 --> 01:31:14,417
I am Silk.

1229
01:31:14,500 --> 01:31:15,708
Silk.

1230
01:31:15,833 --> 01:31:18,417
Don't forget I'm a star.

1231
01:31:19,875 --> 01:31:23,083
When stars fade away, they
become one with the darkness.

1232
01:31:23,167 --> 01:31:25,708
And when the bare darkness strikes...

1233
01:31:25,792 --> 01:31:28,542
the first thing it takes
away is the star's shine.

1234
01:31:44,000 --> 01:31:45,083
Hello...

1235
01:31:45,167 --> 01:31:46,500
Ramakant, please.

1236
01:31:46,875 --> 01:31:48,458
Madam, he is busy at a pooja.
[Religious offering]

1237
01:31:48,542 --> 01:31:49,708
Pooja?

1238
01:31:49,792 --> 01:31:51,250
For what?

1239
01:31:51,708 --> 01:31:54,042
Madam, it's a pooja for his new film.

1240
01:31:54,583 --> 01:31:57,333
Tell Ramakant it's Silk!

1241
01:31:58,708 --> 01:32:00,958
Sorry madam, I can't disturb him.

1242
01:32:13,833 --> 01:32:15,000
Hello...

1243
01:32:15,125 --> 01:32:16,875
Hello, give the phone to Ramakant!

1244
01:32:16,958 --> 01:32:18,083
Madam...

1245
01:32:18,167 --> 01:32:20,417
Tell Ramakant it's Silk!

1246
01:32:23,875 --> 01:32:26,875
It's Silk madam on the line.
She wants to talk to you.

1247
01:32:27,417 --> 01:32:29,083
Tell her I'll call her later.

1248
01:32:29,167 --> 01:32:30,583
Okay.

1249
01:32:33,917 --> 01:32:35,250
I'm sorry, madam.

1250
01:32:35,542 --> 01:32:37,083
I can't disturb him.

1251
01:32:38,500 --> 01:32:39,875
Suryakant sir...

1252
01:32:43,875 --> 01:32:45,292
Sir, I'm very happy.

1253
01:32:45,750 --> 01:32:48,583
One brother will write,
the other will act.

1254
01:32:48,667 --> 01:32:49,792
Today is a great day.

1255
01:32:49,875 --> 01:32:51,167
And Silk will dance.

1256
01:32:54,917 --> 01:32:56,167
Excuse me.

1257
01:32:58,167 --> 01:32:59,333
Vijayan!

1258
01:32:59,458 --> 01:33:00,667
Yes, sir?

1259
01:33:03,417 --> 01:33:04,875
Silk...

1260
01:33:05,333 --> 01:33:07,542
will not act in this film.

1261
01:33:08,542 --> 01:33:11,333
The audience has seen
every inch of her talent.

1262
01:33:11,958 --> 01:33:13,417
Sir, as you wish.

1263
01:33:13,500 --> 01:33:14,625
But sir...

1264
01:33:14,708 --> 01:33:16,708
the public demands excitement.

1265
01:33:17,417 --> 01:33:20,583
We will change the trend.

1266
01:33:21,458 --> 01:33:23,208
Everything that Silk did...

1267
01:33:23,667 --> 01:33:26,625
we'll get the heroine to do.

1268
01:33:27,167 --> 01:33:28,625
That's fine...

1269
01:33:28,708 --> 01:33:30,250
sir but what about
the heroine's image?

1270
01:33:30,708 --> 01:33:33,250
The public goes for the goods on
display, the store doesn't matter.

1271
01:33:34,542 --> 01:33:37,458
when honour is disrobed...

1272
01:33:37,542 --> 01:33:40,750
it's the 'honourable'
ones that enjoy it the most.

1273
01:33:41,500 --> 01:33:43,458
You're right, absolutely right, sir.

1274
01:33:43,958 --> 01:33:46,333
Ramakant, what do you have to say?

1275
01:33:47,125 --> 01:33:48,333
Sir...

1276
01:33:48,417 --> 01:33:49,917
Silk madam on the line.

1277
01:33:52,000 --> 01:33:53,125
Silk...

1278
01:33:53,458 --> 01:33:55,000
what a coincidence.

1279
01:33:56,042 --> 01:33:57,750
We were just talking about you.

1280
01:33:58,417 --> 01:34:00,250
I'm here with Vijayan and Surya.

1281
01:34:01,917 --> 01:34:04,000
They don't want you
for their next film.

1282
01:34:05,292 --> 01:34:07,792
And I think their decision is right.

1283
01:34:09,000 --> 01:34:10,458
You won't do this film.

1284
01:34:10,875 --> 01:34:12,792
Absolutely not!

1285
01:34:13,875 --> 01:34:15,333
On the first day of the shoot...

1286
01:34:16,042 --> 01:34:18,833
I would like to
introduce you to my parents.

1287
01:34:31,750 --> 01:34:33,125
Hello, Silk ma'am.

1288
01:34:33,208 --> 01:34:34,667
I am Mutthu.

1289
01:34:34,750 --> 01:34:36,875
I am a small time film maker.

1290
01:34:37,542 --> 01:34:39,083
I would to work with you.

1291
01:34:39,167 --> 01:34:41,000
This is my card.

1292
01:34:41,083 --> 01:34:42,500
Drop it at my place.

1293
01:34:42,583 --> 01:34:44,708
Okay, thank you very much.

1294
01:34:45,125 --> 01:34:46,333
Excuse me.

1295
01:34:46,833 --> 01:34:48,542
Well, the set is beautiful.

1296
01:34:49,792 --> 01:34:51,167
Congratulations.

1297
01:34:51,708 --> 01:34:53,625
It's all thanks to you.

1298
01:34:56,750 --> 01:34:58,667
And don't make a mess today.

1299
01:34:59,500 --> 01:35:01,417
My parents will be here soon.

1300
01:35:02,917 --> 01:35:04,292
Your mother is fine but...

1301
01:35:04,542 --> 01:35:06,208
how old is your father?

1302
01:35:07,250 --> 01:35:08,792
Silk, please!

1303
01:35:12,542 --> 01:35:13,958
Relax will you!

1304
01:35:14,875 --> 01:35:17,500
I'm a hit with the men in your family.

1305
01:35:20,000 --> 01:35:22,292
You know... I don't like such jokes.

1306
01:35:23,417 --> 01:35:25,542
Ramakant sir...

1307
01:35:27,333 --> 01:35:28,542
One second.

1308
01:35:33,917 --> 01:35:35,208
Silk madam...

1309
01:35:35,833 --> 01:35:38,042
I'm a big fan of yours.

1310
01:35:38,458 --> 01:35:39,667
Thank you.

1311
01:35:39,750 --> 01:35:41,625
I am Shakeela.

1312
01:35:47,750 --> 01:35:49,042
So you're Shakeela!

1313
01:35:49,125 --> 01:35:51,125
You've heard about me?

1314
01:35:51,708 --> 01:35:55,958
Yes, but it was probably a lie.

1315
01:35:56,250 --> 01:35:57,958
Why do you say that?

1316
01:36:01,625 --> 01:36:03,125
Do you have a mirror at home?

1317
01:36:04,292 --> 01:36:05,833
Break it...

1318
01:36:07,208 --> 01:36:10,042
because it's lying that
you can be another Silk.

1319
01:36:13,292 --> 01:36:14,875
You are wrong!

1320
01:36:15,583 --> 01:36:17,833
I'm sure I have something...

1321
01:36:19,125 --> 01:36:22,125
I have the talent.

1322
01:36:25,625 --> 01:36:26,792
Is that so?

1323
01:36:28,000 --> 01:36:29,208
Come on then!

1324
01:37:01,417 --> 01:37:05,083
There is that night of the honeymoon

1325
01:37:05,167 --> 01:37:08,500
I am that night

1326
01:37:08,792 --> 01:37:12,458
The joy of that night

1327
01:37:12,542 --> 01:37:15,000
I am that joy

1328
01:37:15,083 --> 01:37:18,667
That knocks the lover senseless

1329
01:37:18,750 --> 01:37:22,042
I am that intoxication

1330
01:37:22,333 --> 01:37:25,958
The mantra to love and
relationships that you have read

1331
01:37:26,000 --> 01:37:29,333
I am that book

1332
01:37:29,708 --> 01:37:33,125
I am that book.

1333
01:37:33,958 --> 01:37:35,667
I play like the banjo

1334
01:37:35,750 --> 01:37:37,500
I blossom in dreams

1335
01:37:37,583 --> 01:37:41,083
Gentlemen, make me infamous

1336
01:37:41,167 --> 01:37:43,000
I intoxicate you like whiskey

1337
01:37:43,083 --> 01:37:44,833
I grapple like a hiccup

1338
01:37:44,917 --> 01:37:48,417
Get intoxicated, my gentleman

1339
01:37:48,750 --> 01:37:50,542
We forget

1340
